{"id": "0122f1d8c13b8d55cb073e67eeac30a53d12ed8e7a3f4c669a791d578addcc74", "item_id": "73e61a7bc1:0", "text": "RenderMan features robust support for the industry-standard ACES color management system, and other color spaces, such as the popular Filmic Blender, in all bridge products, including the interactive RenderMan Image Tool."}
{"id": "b56dd9fed636684a736e2a5228edcd2ffc457e3f9a8f3bf5d4fe589c8646e5e0", "item_id": "73e61a7bc1:1", "text": "OCIO Configurations"}
{"id": "cb0072e25a33f618e2893be2ad5832a7aaff3435237256c63abea8f2e3092ece", "item_id": "73e61a7bc1:2", "text": "RenderMan ships with a number of OCIO configurations :"}
{"id": "61dd7ef6f091369b64fab73d61e03a0f56b16fef3ce55990d3df57fb6f614a44", "item_id": "73e61a7bc1:3", "text": "LINEAR-sRGB"}
{"id": "0175b818d05b1f09a044cd42b542abe35c302ba30df050bd57202ecb718ee3a0", "item_id": "73e61a7bc1:4", "text": "The original Sony Pictures Imageworks configuration has been used since the dawn of time."}
{"id": "c67c9cae687f60cbd9586b6dc6e8985c4afd3209f73ea76a9ffff08bc6d85ddf", "item_id": "73e61a7bc1:5", "text": "ACES-1.2"}
{"id": "0f2076f394f9b1aac26b139ef1f9a3c490610c9ab2fbd03a4a004da658070ccb", "item_id": "73e61a7bc1:6", "text": "The visual effects standard Academy Colour Encoding System for filmmaking and computer graphics."}
{"id": "5be340263022397c80ffea601d5e424715393247ea320ba0b7fc26dd87f929d9", "item_id": "73e61a7bc1:7", "text": "FILMIC BLENDER"}
{"id": "c19cf78152fa9151aec1672691beba572056d93738306caee6d3b7d87d6fbe87", "item_id": "73e61a7bc1:8", "text": "A popular BT.709-based configuration provides a high dynamic range and other effects typical in film stock. Developed by Troy Sobotka."}
{"id": "ba41a54747c7ef144e4534059c662dfa92fc1b78e0918d5f356d23c5ab280234", "item_id": "73e61a7bc1:9", "text": "Configuration selection"}
{"id": "013d47639e51e2ee1145e4bd503428d8ab62d5379ac2dd354833b63cab0434ca", "item_id": "73e61a7bc1:10", "text": "$OCIO"}
{"id": "aba74e9b00998b4e157c29bab70d74a7c8870de03fe59b8ffec01412f1c20105", "item_id": "73e61a7bc1:11", "text": ": Use the color space defined by your systems environment variable. Typically sRGB."}
{"id": "ca7981b46ecf2c1787b6d76d81d9fd7fa0ca95842e2fcc2a452869891a9334d1", "item_id": "73e61a7bc1:12", "text": "Off"}
{"id": "44539cae8bf1dc8ed726e3d646bd2451ce880be7b7aacb1ca67885f6a8b96839", "item_id": "73e61a7bc1:13", "text": ":  Scene Linear is defined as the scene-wide color space."}
{"id": "b0528e9977d76a735cff7ddd566d12a7972769acfb7e9f213c0b277d87e32026", "item_id": "73e61a7bc1:14", "text": "ACES1.2"}
{"id": "e1ec69849c15cc1ec5e207594d1cc3f6deb179fa70803616cd816a7c6aafd482", "item_id": "73e61a7bc1:15", "text": ": Use the ACES 1.2 color encoding system that ships with RenderMan 24."}
{"id": "dace3d20850eefbe0e5ff6328a577dce6cb3e9beaacdfd79c2a82cb2c5ae7fa9", "item_id": "73e61a7bc1:16", "text": "Filmic Blender"}
{"id": "d51a0a0ed4930249c661b85681eb11098d05fe1cbe5b1b1214c2d4f0481a09eb", "item_id": "73e61a7bc1:17", "text": ": Use the popular BT.709 color space."}
{"id": "494ca78f7374e46fb2de9ad9f2dbd4aaae89b50b2ca044177a1566a59e06627e", "item_id": "73e61a7bc1:18", "text": "Custom"}
{"id": "017516157b3efe46a89cf2681cd7b6ce44e037b8392925c5a1d16967035c90d4", "item_id": "73e61a7bc1:19", "text": ": Allows for a custom color space file to be specified."}
{"id": "5e9a4a56a30ce061a2e8fcba3906c730ba7c4b516dcba69ce7c23a72dab6c269", "item_id": "73e61a7bc1:20", "text": "Please note that you will need to close and re-open IT when switching between OCIO configurations for the new color space to be correctly displayed in IT"}
{"id": "a36bc82ec767afc182eefd36170118784b938d0126f6ac5a106a0f95166e57e2", "item_id": "73e61a7bc1:21", "text": "Color managed items"}
{"id": "608a0e3fe02af3bdc06aee99b1fcdcc6057e8db45fdf4878300348d9990d2c23", "item_id": "73e61a7bc1:22", "text": "UI color values"}
{"id": "3b2ea4a7482480d51394cca60ad3ebcb184af3ceec3d6c90f84c0beb21ea37d0", "item_id": "73e61a7bc1:23", "text": "All DCC apps provide a color-managed color picker that will return a color in the rendering colorspace. RenderMan simply uses them as-is."}
{"id": "18786940ec538ef1c78ee325f06b25dd4de63b135f4050ac39319462c2cb49f5", "item_id": "73e61a7bc1:24", "text": "Lights"}
{"id": "1205cedd335ff95771f7150d3e345a545a0f692bf551998aae28dbb24136e45e", "item_id": "73e61a7bc1:25", "text": "Color Temperature was computed in Rec.709 before 24.0 and is now color-managed."}
{"id": "cb094b4ffe3da3d9ea78fb0b66f7cb1a363b8f012062787ab5c99ef64db2c208", "item_id": "73e61a7bc1:26", "text": "PxrEnvDayLight is also color-managed and relies on the"}
{"id": "103292fd580eeb9fca8fbe49e53abf0d9f55703bb77d36ae4f2e84636f301704", "item_id": "73e61a7bc1:27", "text": "srgb_linear"}
{"id": "41b3a88460344ecec9b9939fe207f0f4bca4e9547b5c757311cd459b2f69ac64", "item_id": "73e61a7bc1:28", "text": "role."}
{"id": "b5779457b3993ccc9cc5712da7d59fa2a633249c2c186c476b838306099e7662", "item_id": "73e61a7bc1:29", "text": "Textures"}
{"id": "f4569ff1962611652fe20edc5d00ba50347bf44af5ace4605fb9b4200fa9c9de", "item_id": "73e61a7bc1:30", "text": "Textures MUST be converted to the"}
{"id": "f748f8d90516c1cecee83006e3c9de6c9117affdf9c6e42e0b450195ed88bac8", "item_id": "73e61a7bc1:38", "text": "rendering"}
{"id": "6ffa5ce2a594d11468fbbf79fb43d24d955d03e5f63b585fc8a316c49cb43c35", "item_id": "73e61a7bc1:32", "text": "color space before usage. This task can be accomplished by the Texture Manager."}
{"id": "b8c1ebfa54aa988403ed0cc1b9bafad68292734c8c20717a835742699d05f11b", "item_id": "73e61a7bc1:33", "text": "It is also possible to use the PxrColorSpace pattern to convert a texture color, but at a performance cost."}
{"id": "160a13d94fb047389d47be363a4de1af8d6f8d2024d1e8c70a62e41ff072669d", "item_id": "73e61a7bc1:34", "text": "Patterns"}
{"id": "284885d9887487a64de8e14c44122079d4c6a09a88c7188668fa2f93a90c7483", "item_id": "73e61a7bc1:35", "text": "PxrBlackBody is color-managed."}
{"id": "433c30a2e09c5a0eb6f31ac94716db28c1241c30fefe73558107be2ec56940ed", "item_id": "73e61a7bc1:36", "text": "PxrHairColor is color-managed."}
{"id": "ce0856e05da72b040b24aab93cfa4c732ed7b029b8cfd5fad8a0b7298922130f", "item_id": "73e61a7bc1:37", "text": "PxrColorSpace allows artists to convert from one color space to the"}
{"id": "71bed6ba9bcb7f27c0dff0023e96e1625f63b56585cdb9dcb75f8a27df1b1f98", "item_id": "73e61a7bc1:39", "text": "space."}
